observations.recommendation:
We reiterated our previous audit recommendations that the Local Chief Executive 

(a) instruct the Inventory Team to undertake complete physical count of all property, plant and equipment and the inventories of the municipality prepare the corresponding Report of the Physical Count of PPE and Inventories and submit the same to the Office of the Auditor within the prescribed period;

(b) instruct the Municipal Accountant to maintain Supplies Ledger Cards and PPE Ledger Cards;



(c) designated Property and Supply Officer to maintain stock cards and property cards for supplies and PPE, respectively; and

(d) require the ICO-Municipal Treasurer, Property and Supply Officer and Municipal Accountant to reconcile their property records after the conduct of physical count to establish correctness of balances of PPE and Inventories accounts.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the OIC-Municipal Accountant to 

(a) stop the practice of granting new cash advances unless the previous cash advance has been liquidated; 

(b) require the concerned personnel to liquidate cash advances as soon as the purpose thereof had been accomplished; 

(c) send demand letters to require liquidation of the cash advances; and 

(d) monitor timely submission of liquidation reports and completeness of supporting documents in accordance with COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive thru the MENRO 
(a) continue to embark effective projects and programs that support the Municipality’s Ecological Solid Waste Management Program to sustain economic development that is in harmony with the environment; 

(b) intensify the information drive and awareness campaign on the regulations on solid waste management in coordination with barangay officials; 

(c) accelerate efforts in the enforcement of “no segregation, no collection” and “no littering” policies; 

(d) take appropriate actions to expedite necessary restoration of the MRFs of Barangay San Juan North, Natividad North and San Fernando Norte; and 

(e) pursue the establishment of MRFs in Barangays San Roque and Bagong Sikat and hasten the construction of MRFs in Barangay Maligaya and Barangay San Fernando Sur to avoid illegal dumping of assorted garbage along barangay roads, public market, drainage, canals and waterways.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the OIC-Municipal Accountant to 

(a) stop the practice of granting new cash advances without the liquidation of previous ones; 

(b) require the concerned personnel to liquidate cash advances as soon as the purpose thereof had been accomplished; 

(c) send demand letters to require liquidation of the cash advances; and 

(d) monitor timely submission of liquidation reports and completeness of supporting documents in accordance with COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the ICO-Municipal Treasurer to 

(a) sign certification in the Cashbooks/CRRec/CDR/CkDR at the end of each month; 

(b) rule and closed the debit and credit at the end of each day; 

(c) write legibly in ink the totals at the end of each day and carry forward as opening balance for the next day; and 

(d) make totals of Debit and Credit column at the end of each month.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the Municipal Accountant to

(a) stop the practice of granting new cash advances without the liquidation of previous ones;

(b) require the concerned personnel to liquidate cash advances as soon as the purpose thereof had been accomplished; 

(c) send demand letters to require liquidation of the cash advances; 

(d) monitor timely submission of liquidation reports and completeness of supporting documents in accordance with COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012; and

(e) avail of the remedial measures provided for in Sections 7.0 and 8.0 regarding the write-off of dormant receivable accounts from former deceased elected officials.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor 
(a) take appropriate action to expedite the construction of the new Material Recovery Facility (MRF) of the Municipality;

(b) ensure that the existing MRF of the seven component Barangays become fully operational;

(c) provide necessary support in enjoining the remaining 16 Barangays to establish their own MRF; 

(d) instruct the Municipal Engineer to prepare separate collection schedules for different types of wastes to avoid mixed collection of wastes;  and

(e) include representatives from the recycling and the manufacturing or packaging industry to be the members of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board (MSWMB).

We therefore reiterated our recommendation that The Local Chief Executive:

instruct the Municipal Treasurer to prepare an updated Certified List of Taxpayers, bearing the names, amount due and collectible during the year, and submit the same to the accounting unit as the basis in setting up of RPT/SEF tax receivable in the succeeding year;

ensure that the list of taxpayers bear vital information, such as the addresses, to facilitate, if necessary, the sending of notices and other follow up communications relative to tax campaign activities and other collection strategy that maybe  implemented by Management;

introduce collection strategy that would significantly help increase the tax collection of the municipality;

direct the Accountant to 

observe the provision under Section 20 of NGAS Manual for LGUs; and

use the Certified List of Taxpayers prepared by the Office of the Municipal Treasurer as the basis in recording the RPT/SET tax receivables at the beginning of the year.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

cause the immediate liquidation of the cash advances granted to LGU officials/employees. See to it that the liquidation reports are submitted to the Office of the COA Auditor for review supported by complete documents, such as the official receipts, certificate of seminar/trainings completed, etc. Henceforth, introduce controls that would assure that cash advances are liquidated or reported as soon as the purpose of the cash advance is served;

endeavor to strengthen internal control practices thru assignment of competent or trusted personnel who will review transactions on an on-going basis for proper monitoring of adherence to prescribed policies and procedures, laws, rules and regulations;

 require the OIC Municipal Accountant to: 

cause the issuance of demand letters to accountable officials/employee for the settlement of their respective accountabilities;
monitor timely submission of liquidation reports and completeness of supporting documents in accordance with COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012; and
refrain from processing cash advances of any officials/employees unless the previous cash advance given to him/her is first settled in accordance with Section 89 of PD No. 1445.
